section.section:
Whenever a petition is filed other than in the county where the child resides, the court, on its own motion or on motion of a party, may transfer the case at any time to any appropriate county, including a county where:
Another case involving custody, visitation, or support of the child is pending;
The child resides;
A parent of the child resides; or
The court determines it is in the child's best interests for further proceedings concerning the child to take place.
